'''2009年H1N1流感大流行'''（英文：2009 H1N1 Pandemic），也称'''2009年猪流感大流行'''（2009 swine flu pandemic），是于2009年春季至2010年8月间发生的一场全球性[[流感大流行|流感大流行]]<ref name="Influenza A(H1N1)" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=2009 H1N1 Pandemic|url=https://www.cdc.gov/flu/pandemic-resources/2009-h1n1-pandemic.html|accessdate=2021-04-05|date=2019-06-11|last=|work=|publisher=[[美国疾控中心|美国疾控中心]]（US CDC）|language=en-us|archive-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318191813/https://www.cdc.gov/flu/pandemic-resources/2009-h1n1-pandemic.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2009 H1N1 Influenza - an overview|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/2009-h1n1-influenza|accessdate=2021-04-06|work=|publisher=Science Direct|language=en|archive-date=2021-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210605013536/https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/2009-h1n1-influenza|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=谈谈2009年H1N1流感大流行|url=https://share.america.gov/zh-hans/the-2009-h1n1-pandemic-and-how-the-u-s-responded-to-the-outbreak/|accessdate=2021-04-05|date=2020-02-21|last=|work=|publisher=ShareAmerica （[[美国国务院|美国国务院]]下属）|language=zh-hans|archive-date=2021-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210605011104/https://share.america.gov/zh-hans/the-2009-h1n1-pandemic-and-how-the-u-s-responded-to-the-outbreak/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此次[[大流行|大流行]]是最近一次由[[甲型H1N1流感病毒|甲型H1N1流感病毒]]引起的流感大流行，第一次是1918年的[[西班牙流感|西班牙流感]]，第二次是[[1977年俄国流感|1977年俄国流感]]<ref name=":02">{{Cite web|title=Influenza Pandemic Plan. The Role of WHO and Guidelines for National and Regional Planning|url=https://www.who.int/csr/resources/publications/influenza/whocdscsredc991.pdf|accessdate=2021-01-28|date=April 1999|publisher=[[世界卫生组织|World Health Organization]]|pages=38, 41|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201203084733/https://www.who.int/csr/resources/publications/influenza/whocdscsredc991.pdf|archivedate=2020-12-03|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":12">{{Cite journal|title=中国流感大流行的百年历史|author=秦颖 等|url=http://html.rhhz.net/zhlxbx/20180803.htm|journal=《中华流行病学杂志》（''Chinese Journal of Epidemiology''）|accessdate=2021-01-28|issue=8|year=2018|volume=39|page=1028-1031|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109065742/http://html.rhhz.net/zhlxbx/20180803.htm|archivedate=2021-01-09|deadurl=no}}</ref>。

此次大流行的最早已知病例是2009年3月9日[[墨西哥|墨西哥]][[韋拉克魯斯市|韋拉克魯斯市]]格羅利亞的五歲小孩<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lacey|first=Marc|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/04/29/world/americas/29mexico.html|title=From Édgar, 5, Coughs Heard Round the World|date=2009-04-28|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-02-21|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202014813/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/04/29/world/americas/29mexico.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NYT6-23">{{Cite news | last = McNeil, Jr. | first = Donald G. | title = In New Theory, Swine Flu Started in Asia, Not Mexico | work = The New York Times | date = 2009-06-23 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2009/06/24/health/24flu.html | accessdate = 2009-09-01 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090807164633/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/06/24/health/24flu.html | archivedate = 2009-08-07 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。17日開始有[[美國|美國]]病例，並於4月12日發生小範圍群聚感染<ref>{{cite web |author1=Central of Disease Control and Prevention |title=Outbreak of Swine-Origin Influenza A (H1N1) Virus Infection --- Mexico, March--April 2009 |url=https://www.cdc.gov/mmwR/preview/mmwrhtml/mm58d0430a2.htm |website=Central of Disease Control and Prevention |accessdate=2020-02-01 |archive-date=2009-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090606130423/http://www.cdc.gov/MMWR/preview/mmwrhtml/mm58d0430a2.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。4月15日於美國確診首例病患，疫情開始在[[美國|美國]][[加利福尼亞州|加利福尼亞州]]、[[德克薩斯州|德克薩斯州]]多处快速爆發，其後向墨西哥與美國以外的國家输出案例，疫情不斷蔓延<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/30386163/#storyContinued|title=Mexico flu deaths raise fears of global epidemic|publisher=MSNBC|date=2009-04-24|accessdate=2009-04-24|language=en|archive-date=2009-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090425133921/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/30386163#storyContinued|dead-url=no}}</ref>。经估计，持续了一年多的疫情导致全球214个国家约7亿到14亿人感染<ref>{{Cite web|title=Study puts global 2009 H1N1 infection rate at 11% to 21%|url=http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2011/08/study-puts-global-2009-h1n1-infection-rate-11-21|accessdate=2020-03-20|last=Aug 08|first=Robert Roos {{!}}|work=CIDRAP|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125151837/https://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2011/08/study-puts-global-2009-h1n1-infection-rate-11-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>，约150,000到575,000人死亡<ref>{{Cite web|title=First Global Estimates of 2009 H1N1 Pandemic Mortality Released by CDC-Led Collaboration {{!}} CDC|url=https://www.cdc.gov/flu/spotlights/pandemic-global-estimates.htm|accessdate=2020-03-20|date=2019-11-20|work=www.cdc.gov|language=en-us|archive-date=2020-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303012120/https://www.cdc.gov/flu/spotlights/pandemic-global-estimates.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其中有明确统计的死亡病例约1.85万人<ref>{{cite news|title=世卫组织应对甲流疫情评估报告出台|url=http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlnews/2011/3/245573.shtm|accessdate=2011-03-29|newspaper=科学网|date=2011-03-29|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130022143/http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlnews/2011/3/245573.shtm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但世界卫生组织称实际死亡人数「毫无疑问更高」<ref>{{Cite web|title=WHO {{!}} Pandemic (H1N1) 2009 - update 100|url=https://www.who.int/csr/don/2010_05_14/en/|accessdate=2020-03-20|work=WHO|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127213417/https://www.who.int/csr/don/2010_05_14/en/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=H1N1 Still A Pandemic, Says WHO|url=https://www.redorbit.com/news/health/1893907/h1n1_still_a_pandemic_says_who/|accessdate=2020-03-20|date=2010-07-20|work=Redorbit|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122141411/https://www.redorbit.com/news/health/1893907/h1n1_still_a_pandemic_says_who/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2013年公布的数据显示，在流感季中，全世界每5人中就有1人感染甲型H1N1流感，但死亡率可能不到0.02%<ref>{{cite news|title=华人体内存在特殊基因 易感染H1N1流感病毒|url=http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlnews/2013/2/274529.shtm|accessdate=2013-02-01|newspaper=科学网|date=2013-02-01|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928193326/http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlnews/2013/2/274529.shtm|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。2009年5月底，該流感在墨西哥死亡率達2%，但在墨西哥以外死亡率僅0.1%。另据[[美国疾病控制与预防中心|美国CDC]]估计，截至2010年3月中旬，这场疫情导致5900万美国人染病，26万5千人住院，1万2千人死亡。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2010/mar/19/science/la-sci-swine-flu20-2010mar20 |title=2010年3月19日《洛杉矶时报》：“According to the latest CDC estimates, released a week ago, about 59 million Americans contracted swine flu, 265,000 were hospitalized as a result, and 12,000 died.” |accessdate=2013年8月13日 |archive-date=2010年3月23日 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323061750/http://articles.latimes.com/2010/mar/19/science/la-sci-swine-flu20-2010mar20 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

由於未能為所有個案作檢測，所以[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]把所有病例統稱為疑似流感疾病。而這些病例都有嚴重的疑似流感病徵，甚至肺炎病徵，譬如墨西哥的病例更導致死亡。這個新變種甲型流感病毒基因包括人類[[流感病毒|流感病毒]]、[[豬流感|豬流感]]及[[禽流感|禽流感]]<ref name="NewSci-20090424-pandemic">{{cite news|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17025-deadly-new-flu-virus-in-us-and-mexico-may-go-pandemic.html|title=Deadly new flu virus in US and Mexico may go pandemic|work=[[New_Scientist|New Scientist]]|date=2009-04-24|accessdate=2009-04-26|language=en|archive-date=2009-04-28|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5gNd9HTT9?url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17025-deadly-new-flu-virus-in-us-and-mexico-may-go-pandemic.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。4月底，世界衛生組織和[[美國疾病控制與預防中心|美國疾病控制與預防中心]]對於新變種，疑似人傳人的風險及在墨西哥的高致命性都表示十分關注。4月25日，世衛總幹事[[陳馮富珍|陳馮富珍]]宣布把這次疫情定位為「國際關注的突發公共衛生事件」，其原因是對於病例中的臨床、流行病學及病毒學報告缺乏認識。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090425/en/index.html|title=Swine influenza|date=2009-04-25|accessdate=2009-05-01|publisher=世界衛生組織|archive-date=2013-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202223414/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090425/en/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2010年8月10日，[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]在其紧急咨询委员会15名独立科学家发出建议后，宣布H1N1甲型流感大流行已经结束。<ref>[http://www.zaobao.com/gj/gj100811_004.shtml 世卫组织宣布 H1N1流感结束] {{Wayback|url=http://www.zaobao.com/gj/gj100811_004.shtml |date=20190822021351 }}，聯合早報網，2010-08-11{{zh-sg}}</ref>

== 病徵 ==
此次甲型H1N1流感的主要病徵有：發燒（高於攝氏37.8度）、肌肉疼痛、咳嗽、喉嚨痛、鼻塞，甚至[[嘔吐|嘔吐]]和像[[痢疾|痢疾]]的病徵。<ref name="g_ap_0426">{{cite news|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5g-G1kSAM9yaH00eBrXD2S5s-3ZhgD97Q9LPG0|title=Canada confirms 4 swine flu cases among students|publisher=Google/AP|date=2009-04-26|accessdate=2009-04-27|archive-date=2009-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090503031625/http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5g-G1kSAM9yaH00eBrXD2S5s-3ZhgD97Q9LPG0|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 传播情况 ==
[[File:AntigenicShift_HiRes_vector.svg|270px]]
=== 原因 ===
美國疾病控制及預防中心與世界衛生組織對這次爆發可能演變成全球瘟疫表示十分憂慮，其原因如下<ref name="CDCBriefing_Besser_20090424">Besser, Richard, Acting Director CDC. [http://www.cdc.gov/media/transcripts/2009/t090424.htm CDC Press Transcript April 24, 2009 (unedited)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cdc.gov/media/transcripts/2009/t090424.htm |date=20090428151540 }}: "<nowiki>there are really three things we want to look for when we’re thinking about whether a virus is causing a new pandemic...</nowiki>".</ref>：

;新變種:這個流感病毒是全新品種，所以人類沒有對抗它的疫苗或者有先天性免疫力<ref name="CDC_MMWRDispatch_20090421">U.S. Centers for Disease Control. [http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/mm58d0421a1.htm Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report Dispatch, April 21, 2009] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/mm58d0421a1.htm |date=20090925183214 }}.</ref>。

;人傳人:這個病毒似乎可以人傳人。根據調查，病人沒有直接接觸豬隻<ref name="who_don_2009-04-24">{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/csr/don/2009_04_24/en/index.html|title=Influenza-Like Illness in the United States and Mexico|publisher=World Health Organization|date=2009-04-24|accessdate=2009-04-25|archive-date=2009-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090427070549/http://www.who.int/csr/don/2009_04_24/en/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。新變種將可能證實為人傳人<ref name="CDC-QA-AndYou-20090427">{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/swineflu/swineflu_you.htm |title=Questions & Answers: Swine Influenza and You |publisher=CDC.gov |date=2009-04-27 |accessdate=2009-04-27 |archive-date=2009-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091006101009/http://www.cdc.gov/swineflu/swineflu_you.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但是，最少有另外一個豬流感的變種曾經人傳人而沒有引起社區感染<ref name="CDC-QA-KeyFacts-20090424">{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/swineflu/key_facts.htm |title=Questions & Answers: Key Facts about Swine Influenza (Swine Flu) |publisher=CDC.gov |date=2009-04-24 |accessdate=2009-04-27 |archive-date=2019-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930192428/https://www.cdc.gov/swineflu/key_facts.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。相反地，例如，上一次在人類爆發的[[禽流感|禽流感]]的傳播差不多可以確認完全是由直接接觸鳥類而感染。

;毒性: 病毒毒性導致墨西哥境內的受害者病情嚴重，甚至死亡。再者，墨西哥境內的豬流感主要攻擊年輕健康的成年人，就像1918年的[[西班牙流感|西班牙流感]]<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2009/04/25/world/americas/25mexico.html?bl&ex=1240891200&en=ce91d53e13153eed&ei=5087 Fighting Deadly Flu, Mexico Shuts Schools] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/04/25/world/americas/25mexico.html?bl&ex=1240891200&en=ce91d53e13153eed&ei=5087 |date=20201130150756 }}, The New York times, 24 April 2009.</ref>。大部分其他的變種會在兒童、老人及免疫力低的人士產生嚴重病徵<ref name="WashingtonPost_20090425">Stein, Rob and Brown, David. Washington Post (April 25, 2009). [http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/04/24/AR2009042404075.html Swine Flu Found in Mexican Outbreak] {{Wayback|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/04/24/AR2009042404075.html |date=20201218034148 }}</ref><ref name="who_don_2009-04-24"/>。
;地理: 病毒在眾多地區被發現，顯示控制措施難以施行<ref name="CDC-Press-20090425-Investigation">{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/media/transcripts/2009/t090425.htm |title=CDC Press Briefing Transcript - Media Availability on CDC Investigation of Human Cases of Swine Influenza |publisher=CDC |date=2009-04-25 |accessdate=2009-04-26 |archive-date=2020-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125203648/https://www.cdc.gov/media/transcripts/2009/t090425.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name"NewSci-20090424-pandemic">{{cite news|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17025-deadly-new-flu-virus-in-us-and-mexico-may-go-pandemic.html|title=Deadly new flu virus in US and Mexico may go pandemic|work=[[New_Scientist|New Scientist]]|date=2009-04-24|accessdate=2009-04-26|archive-date=2009-04-28|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5gNd9HTT9?url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17025-deadly-new-flu-virus-in-us-and-mexico-may-go-pandemic.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。病毒的潛伏期導致疫情惡化。
;季節性: 具有高毒性的病毒會更快的殺死宿主，導致病毒無法即時的將自己傳播給其它宿主，導致短期間疫情會有降低的跡象。由於宿主死亡率下降，侥幸存活下来的弱毒性病毒更容易在人群中傳播，反而提供病毒更多的突變機會。此外流感病毒不適合在高溫潮濕的環境中生存，於低溫乾燥的氣候才適合大量繁殖，因此流感多半在春季發生，夏季疫情降低，秋冬交替之際則疫情攀升。
;缺乏數據
:仍然存在其他未知的因素，譬如傳播速度、模式、現時對抗流感措施的成效。新變種的不可預測導致評估難以進行<ref>{{cite news|author=陳馮富珍（Chan, Margaret）|date=2009-04-25|title=Statement by WHO Director-General, Dr Margaret Chan: Swine influenza|publisher=世界衛生組織|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090425/en/index.html|accessdate=2009-04-26|language=en|archive-date=2013-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202223414/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090425/en/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 流感大流行警戒级别 ===
{{seealso|流感大流行警告}}

根据[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]规定，流感大流行警戒共有六大级别。

2009年4月27日，世界衛生組織總幹事[[陳馮富珍|陳馮富珍]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_pandemic_phase6_20090611/zh/index.html|title=世界现在处在2009年流感大流行的开端|publisher=世界卫生组织|author=陈冯富珍博士|date=2009-06-11|accessdate=2009-06-11|archive-date=2009-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090614091847/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_pandemic_phase6_20090611/zh/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>博士發表聲明，將警戒由第三級提升為第四級<ref name="who_statement_20090427">{{cite news|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090427/zh/index.html|title=豬流感|publisher=世界衛生組織|author=陳馮富珍|date=2009-04-27|accessdate=2009-04-28|archive-date=2014-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204040956/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2009/h1n1_20090427/zh/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>；同年4月29日，世界衛生組織將流感大流行警戒提升為第五級<ref name="cnn_who_raises_20090429">{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/HEALTH/04/29/swine.flu/index.html|title=WHO raises pandemic alert to second-highest level|publisher=CNN.com|date=2009-04-29|accessdate=2009-04-29|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126050546/http://www.cnn.com/2009/HEALTH/04/29/swine.flu/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，情況罕見。6月11日，正式將警戒級別提升至最高的第六級<ref>{{cite news|url=http://app2.rthk.org.hk/pda/news/content.php?id=588469|title="世衞將全球流感大流行警戒級別升至6級。|publisher=世衞將全球流感大流行警戒級別升至6級|date=2009-06-11|accessdate=2009-06-11}}{{dead link|date=2018年3月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>，是自1968年（[[香港流感|香港流感]] － H3N2）後，41年的第一次。世界衛生組織表示，將流行病警戒級別提升至第六級不代表病毒毒性有所增強，而只是反映出全球各地的感染情況（第六級 － 全球有至少兩個地區或國家出現持續的社區感染：社區爆發）。另外，世衛又表示，會將第六級分為A（輕微）、B（一般）、C（嚴重）三級，每個國家和地區會得到不同的分級。

