H1N1疫苗最初在美国供不应求，[[疾病预防控制中心|疾病预防控制中心]]建议初始剂量应用于孕妇、照顾半岁以下的婴儿的人、半岁至四岁的儿童和医护工作者<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdc.gov/mmWR/PDF/rr/rr5810.pdf|title=Use of Influenza A (H1N1) 2009 Monovalent Vaccine: Recommendations of the Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices (ACIP), 2009|work=[[Morbidity_and_Mortality_Weekly_Report|Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report]]|publisher=[[Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention|Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC)|date=2009-11-28|accessdate=2009-11-02|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091103202202/http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/pdf/rr/rr5810.pdf|archivedate=2009-11-03|deadurl=no}}</ref>。英国国民保健服务建议，疫苗应优先供给有患上[[季节性流感|季节性流感]]临床风险的半岁以上人群、免疫力差的家庭<ref name="nhs-april">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nhs.uk/news/2009/04april/pages/swineflulatest.aspx|title=Swine flu latest from the NHS|date=2009-09-25|work=NHS Choices|publisher=National Health Services|accessdate=2009-09-28|agency=NHS Knowledge Service|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091008013912/http://www.nhs.uk/News/2009/04April/Pages/swineflulatest.aspx|archivedate=2009-10-08|deadurl=no}}</ref>。

尽管最初有人认为需注射两剂疫苗才能见效，但临床试验表明新型疫苗“仅需一剂就能保护成年人，而非两剂”，因此一旦被预言，就会给每人限量供应两剂疫苗<ref name=NYT9-12-09>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/09/11/health/11vaccine.html|title=One Vaccine Shot Seen as Protective for Swine Flu|last=McNeil, Jr.|first=Donald G.|date=2009-09-10|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2009-09-17|archive-date=2009-10-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091007164052/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/09/11/health/11vaccine.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/csr/disease/swineflu/notes/briefing_20091030/en/index.html|title=Experts advise WHO on pandemic vaccine policies and strategies|date=2009-10-30|publisher=[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]|accessdate=2009-11-02|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091102051824/http://www.who.int/csr/disease/swineflu/notes/briefing_20091030/en/index.html|archivedate=2009-11-02|deadurl=no}}</ref>。尽管大多数流感症状轻微，持续数天就会自愈，但世界各地的卫生官员还是担心新病毒容易变异，变得更致命。官员们呼吁社区、企业及个人制定为学校关闭、多位员工因病缺勤、医院病患汹涌及其他疫情大规模爆发的可能影响，制定应急计划<ref name="WSJ-7-18-09">{{Cite news|url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB124787226825260533.html|title=New Push in H1N1 Flu Fight Set for Start of Schoo|last=McKay|first=Betsy|date=2009-07-18|newspaper=[[华尔街日报|华尔街日报]]|accessdate=2009-08-31|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5jeG4aNty?url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB124787226825260533.html?mod=googlenews_wsj|archivedate=2009-09-09|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

2010年2月，疾病预防控制中心免疫实践咨询委员会，投票表决向超过半岁的人群发放万能流感疫苗通过。2010年-2011年的疫苗将有效防止2009年H1N1流感病毒和两个其他流感病毒<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/flu/about/qa/1011_vac_selection.htm |title=Vaccine Selection for the 2010–2011 Influenza Season |publisher=[[U.S._Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention|U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC) |accessdate=2010-08-25 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101006224851/http://www.cdc.gov/flu/about/qa/1011_vac_selection.htm |archivedate=2010-10-06 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

